The formula for calculating the cross-validation error using Leave-One-Out Cross-Validation (LOOCV) in machine learning, as discussed in the context of estimating mean squared error (MSE) for predicting miles per gallon (mpg) using polynomial functions of horsepower on the Auto dataset is given by: 

Formula -> C V_{<n>} = \frac{1}{n} \sum_{i=1}^{n} \left( \frac{y_{i} - \hat{y}_{i}}{1 - h_{i}} \right)^{2} 

Solution -> C V sub n equals 1 over n times the sum from i equals 1 to n of the quantity y sub i minus y hat sub i divided by 1 minus h sub i all squared.
